 Saraki. Photo/Twitter/NGRSenate  Former Senate President Bukola Saraki has faulted the court ruling, which ordered the interim forfeiture of two of his properties in Ikoyi, Lagos State.
  
He said the court must have been misled into granting the order, as neither him nor his lawyers were aware of any application by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) for any forfeiture order.
  
The order followed an ex-parte motion filed by the EFCC, praying the court to deliver the verdict in the interest of justice. Read More: Court misled into granting temporary forfeiture order, says Saraki  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .